events.name: Texas Longhorns at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.description: David Ash threw two fourth-quarter touchdown passes, the last a 36-yard strike to Marquise Goodwin with 2:24 left, to give Texas a 31-27 comeback victory over No. 15 Oregon State in the Valero Alamo Bowl on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas rallies to stun Oregon St.

events.name: Rice Owls at Air Force Falcons

headlines.description: Freshman quarterback Driphus Jackson threw for 264 yards in relief of Rice's hurt starter, including two touchdown passes to Jordan Taylor, and the Owls beat Air Force 33-14 in the Armed Forces Bowl on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Freshman backup sparks Rice vs. Air Force

events.name: West Virginia Mountaineers at Syracuse Orange

headlines.description: Prince-Tyson Gulley ran for 208 yards and had three touchdowns, Syracuse scored twice on safeties and the Orange bid a snow-covered farewell to the Big East with a 38-14 victory over West Virginia in the Pinstripe Bowl on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gulley (3 TDs) carries Cuse by WVU

events.name: Navy Midshipmen at Arizona State Sun Devils

headlines.description: Taylor Kelly threw four touchdown passes and ran for a fifth score to lead Arizona State to its first bowl win in seven years, a 62-28 victory over Navy in the Kraft Fight Hunger Bowl on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arizona St. rolls to first bowl win in 7 years

events.name: TCU Horned Frogs at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Michigan State rallied to beat Texas Christian 17-16 in the Buffalo Wild Wings Bowl on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Michigan St. tops TCU on late FG
